 I. Mr frisky being the nice and energetic person he is, kept pissing mrs. frisky off by giving up their spot in line to other people, so that he could go on the ride at the same time as water-paranoia and I. Oh mr. frisky what\'re we ever gonna do about you smh. Well, this led to one whimsical of a conversation, where we all started roasting mr. frisky and saying, how mrs. frisky should\'ve left him at home with the dogs and went on all the rides by herself. She agreed, and this went on for quite some time. Poor mr frisky tsk tsk tsk. But mr. frisky wasn\'t the only one who got ridiculed. We would occasionally pretend to let other people ahead of us, just to see mrs frisky\'s reaction, which might I say was pretty amusing considering the fact that we were standing in lines for who knows how long. But once we got on the rides, it was all worth it in the end. From the buildup of the ride slowly making its way to the top, to the harmony of our blatant screams of it making its way down the drop (where by the way mrs. frisky would throw her hands in the air, even after being told again and again not to by the management. Something about life being too short she would say) was all worth it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"dropCap\":true,\"backgroundColor\":\"very-light-gray\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-background has-drop-cap has-very-light-gray-background-color\">Moving on, a few rides later, came the water log rides, where now the infamous water-paranoia accidently \"joked\" about how he hates getting wet.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"textColor\":\"very-light-gray\",\"customBackgroundColor\":\"#0c51e9\"} -->\n<p style=\"background-color:#0c51e9\" class=\"has-text-color has-background has-very-light-gray-color\"><em>And this is where he came to be known as \"Water-Paranoia\".</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"backgroundColor\":\"very-light-gray\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-background has-very-light-gray-background-color\">He quickly regretted his words, as he was made to take the front seat. Lets just say, he wasn\'t the most driest one by the time we left the park.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"backgroundColor\":\"very-light-gray\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-background has-very-light-gray-background-color\">In case you are wondering, no we are not rude to each other, rather that is our way of living in the present. Even if it means standing in those LOOOONG ass lines, we would find a way to make them less boring.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"has-text-color has-luminous-vivid-orange-color has-custom-weight\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-color has-luminous-vivid-orange-color has-custom-weight\"><em>To Be Continued ... </em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'My Summer 2K19 Six Flags', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '147-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-09-03 00:22:48', '2019-09-03 05:22:48', '', 147, 'https://blog.danishnaseemoid.com/blog/2019/09/03/147-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
